article.headline: Huff's 29 points lead Chattanooga past Wofford 81-65

images.name: Randy Brady makes a great defensive play for the steal
images.caption: Randy Brady makes a great defensive play for the steal

article.linkText: Huff's 29 points lead Chattanooga past Wofford 81-65
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- — Honor Huff scored 29 points and made five 3-pointers to help Chattanooga defeat Wofford 81-65 on Wednesday night. Huff had five assists for the Mocs (19-9, 11-4 Southern Conference). Jan Zidek scored 15 points while going 5 of 9 (3 for 6 from 3-point range). Sam Alexis finished 3 of 6 from the field to finish with eight points. Corey Tripp led the way for the Terriers (15-13, 8-7) with 21 points. Kyler Filewich added 10 points, six rebounds and five assists for Wofford. Dillon Bailey also had 10 points. Chattanooga took the lead with 3:41 remaining in the first half and did not relinquish it. The score was 39-38 at halftime, with Huff racking up 13 points. Huff scored a team-high 16 points in the second half. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
